article.description: Malik Ellison had 29 points as Hartford beat Stony Brook 65-54 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Ellison scores 29 to lead Hartford past Stony Brook 65-54
article.linkText: Ellison scores 29 to lead Hartford past Stony Brook 65-54
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Malik Ellison had 29 points as Hartford beat Stony Brook 65-54 on Wednesday night. Traci Carter had seven steals for Hartford (16-14, 9-6 America East Conference). Moses Flowers, the Hawks' second leading scorer coming into the contest at 11 points per game, was held to four points. He was 0 of 4 from 3-point range. Makale Foreman had 18 points for the Seawolves (18-11, 9-5). Andrew Garcia added 14 points and 10 rebounds. Jeff Otchere had 10 points and three blocks. The Hawks improve to 2-0 against the Seawolves on the season. Hartford defeated Stony Brook 68-65 on Jan. 15. Hartford finishes out the regular season against Maine at home on Tuesday. Stony Brook faces Albany on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
